13/10/2004
POIANA BRASOV, Romania -- A two-day informal meeting of NATO's defence ministers started in the resort of Poiana Brasov on Wednesday (13 October). Ministers of the 26 member states are expected to discuss operational capabilities and Alliance missions. The NATO-Russia Council is also to convene within the framework of this event. (Nine o' clock - 13/10/04; AP - 12/10/04)
